HEADWORD: Pounding
<hw>Pound"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of beating, bruising, or breaking up; a beating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pounded or pulverized substance.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Covered with the <xex>poundings</xex> of these
rocks.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. S. Blackie.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poundkeeper</ent>⟦br⟧
